cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with text preprocessing and its impact on the performance of a text classifier based on convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The evaluation of the text classifier involves standard benchmarks, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of neural networks makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
